Oh, not very often. Not very often, we used to have to - make them do. I can remember paying two threefarthings a yard - for a dress - two threefarthings and we'd have three dresses - and mak
e three yards for a frock or three and a half yards and so - for half a crown you'd get a dress you see like that, making it yourself. And I can remember - when I wanted to be confirmed - that was before I was married you know, and - and you had to have w
h
ite dresses when you're confirmed, and my mother said, you can only be confirmed if you buy your own - dress and make it. And that was two threefarthings a yard, and - and I can remember it was white with a little silk stripe in it. Full sleeves you know 
with a lace hanging down. And I had - and that was my confirmation dress. And that cost about half a crown you see, but - mm.
